description:
&lt;p&gt;Oxford Health Trust have an exciting opportunity for a part time Family Therapist, to join the South CAMHS Getting More Help Service. The lucky candidate will have the opportunity to work within an established and well regarded CAMHS team, delivering a service to the local community. The role will include working within the South Getting More Help and South Getting Help teams as one south locality. The role will include working within the Family Therapy team, offering family therapy routine clinics, family therapy Complex case clinics, offering consultation, taking part in research and the development of the family therapy provision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also offer clinical supervision, support the development of junior staff, support trainees, take part in the duty rota, Care Coordinate a case load, contribute to peer supervision and complete both routine and urgent assessments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main office is based at the Clockhouse which is in Abingdon on Thames. Abingdon is a market town located in the South of Oxfordshire. It is conveniently situated 1 mile from the A34, 3 miles from Didcot with its train links and 5 miles from the historic city of Oxford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKelly GarsideJob titleClinical Team ManagerEmail addressKelly.garside@oxfordhealth.nhs.ukTelephone number01865-904700&lt;/p&gt;
